This paper discusses time synchronization in vehicular ad hoc networks (VANETs), which is a subfield of computer networks and communication systems. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses precision, accuracy, availability, scalability, and compatibility, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper addresses security issues in VANETs, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the advantages of Global Navigation Satellite System (GNSS) in VANET time synchronization, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
